#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:48
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description"
msgstr "Opis"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid "&kate; is the &kde; Advanced Text Editor."
msgstr "&kate; je &kde; Napredni urejevalnik besedil."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:50
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kate; also provides the editor part for various applications, under the "
"name &kwrite;."
msgstr ""
"&kate; ponuja tudi urejevalnik za različne aplikacije pod imenom &kwrite;."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some of &kate;'s many features include configurable syntax highlighting for "
"languages ranging from C and C++ to &HTML; to bash scripts, the ability to "
"create and maintain projects, a multiple document interface (<acronym>MDI</"
"acronym>), and a self-contained terminal emulator."
msgstr ""
"Nekatere od številnih funkcij &kate; vključujejo nastavljivo označevanje "
"sintakse za jezike, od C in C++ do &HTML; za razbijanje skriptov, možnost "
"ustvarjanja in vzdrževanja projektov, vmesnik za več dokumentov "
"(<acronym>MDI</acronym>) in samostojen emulator terminala."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:59
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"But &kate; is more than a programmer's editor. Its ability to open several "
"files at once makes it ideal for editing &UNIX;'s many configuration files. "
"This document was written in &kate;."
msgstr ""
"Toda &kate; je več kot programerski urejevalnik. Zaradi njegove zmožnosti "
"odpiranja več datotek hkrati je idealen za urejanje številnih "
"konfiguracijskih datotek &UNIX;. Ta dokument je bil napisan v &kate;."

#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Opcije"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<option>-s</option>, <option>--start</option> <replaceable>name</replaceable>"
msgstr ""
"<option>-s</option>, <option>--začetek</option> <replaceable>ime</"
"replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start &kate; with a given session."
msgstr "Zaženi &kate; z določeno sejo."

#. Tag: option
#: man-kate.1.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "--startanon"
msgstr "--startanon"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "Start &kate; with a new anonymous session, implies <option>-n</option>."
msgstr "Zaženi &kate; z novo anonimno sejo pomeni <option>-n</option>."

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-n</option>, <option>--new</option>"
msgstr "<option>-n</option>, <option>--novo</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Force start of a new &kate; instance (is ignored if <option>start</option> "
"is used and another &kate; instance already has the given session opened), "
"forced if no parameters and no URLs are given at all."
msgstr ""
"Vsili zagon novega &kate; primerek (je prezrt, če je uporabljen "
"<option>start</option> in je drug primerek &kate; že odprl dano sejo), "
"vsiljen, če niso podani nobeni parametri ali URL-ji."

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-b</option>, <option>--block</option>"
msgstr "<option>-b</option>, <option>--blokiraj</option>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If using an already running &kate; instance, block until it exits, if URLs "
"given to open."
msgstr ""
"Če uporabljate že delujoč &kate; primer, blokira, dokler ne zapre, če so URL-"
"ji dani za odpiranje."

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-p, --pid</option> <replaceable> pid</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-p, --pid</option> <replaceable> pid</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Only try to reuse kate instance with this <replaceable>pid</replaceable> (is "
"ignored if <option>start</option> is used and another &kate; instance "
"already has the given session opened)."
msgstr ""
"Poskusite ponovno uporabiti samo primerek kate s tem <replaceable>pid</"
"replaceable> (je prezrt, če je uporabljen <option>začni</option> in je drug "
"primerek &kate; že odprl dano sejo)."

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-e, --encoding</option> <replaceable> name</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-e, --encoding</option> <replaceable> ime</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Set encoding for the file to open."
msgstr "Nastavite kodiranje za odpiranje datoteke."

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use this to force a file opened in utf-8 format, for instance. (The "
"command <command>iconv -l</command> provides a list of encodings, which may "
"be helpful to you.)"
msgstr ""
"To lahko uporabite za prisilno odpiranje datoteke v formatu utf-8, na "
"primer. (Ukaz <command>iconv -l</command> ponuja seznam kodiranj, ki vam "
"lahko koristi.)"

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-l, --line</option> <replaceable> line</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-l, --line</option> <replaceable>line</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid "Navigate to this line."
msgstr "Pomaknite se do te vrstice."

#. Tag: term
#: man-kate.1.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid "<option>-c, --column</option> <replaceable> column</replaceable>"
msgstr "<option>-c, --column</option> <replaceable> stolpec</replaceable>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid "Navigate to this column."
msgstr "Pomaknite se do tega stolpca."

#. Tag: option
#: man-kate.1.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid "-i, --stdin"
msgstr "-i, --stdin"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:117
#, no-c-format
msgid "Read the contents of <filename>stdin</filename>."
msgstr "Preberite vsebino <filename>stdin</filename>."

#. Tag: option
#: man-kate.1.docbook:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "--tempfile"
msgstr "--začasna datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:122
#, no-c-format
msgid "The files/&URL;s opened by the application will be deleted after use."
msgstr "Datoteke/&URL;-ji, ki jih odpre aplikacija, bodo po uporabi izbrisani."

#. Tag: replaceable
#: man-kate.1.docbook:126
#, no-c-format
msgid "file"
msgstr "datoteka"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid "File to open."
msgstr "Datoteka za odpiranje."

#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:134
#, no-c-format
msgid "See Also"
msgstr "Poglej tudi"

#. Tag: member
#: man-kate.1.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"More detailed user documentation is available from <ulink url=\"help:/kate"
"\">help:/kate</ulink> (either enter this &URL; into &konqueror;, or run "
"<userinput><command>khelpcenter</command> <parameter>help:/kate</parameter></"
"userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"Podrobnejša uporabniška dokumentacija je na voljo na <ulink url=\"help:/kate"
"\">help:/kate</ulink> (bodisi vnesite ta &URL; v &konqueror; ali zaženite "
"<userinput><command>khelpcenter</command> <parameter>help:/kate</parameter></"
"userinput>)."

#. Tag: member
#: man-kate.1.docbook:141
#, no-c-format
msgid "kf6options(7)"
msgstr "kf6options(7)"

#. Tag: member
#: man-kate.1.docbook:142
#, no-c-format
msgid "qt6options(7)"
msgstr "qt6options(7)"

#. Tag: member
#: man-kate.1.docbook:143
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There is also further information available at the <ulink url=\"https://kate-"
"editor.org/\">&kate; website</ulink>."
msgstr ""
"Dodatne informacije so na voljo tudi na <ulink url=\"https://kate-editor.org/"
"\">&kate; spletno mesto</ulink>."

#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid "Examples"
msgstr "Primeri"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To open a file named <filename>source.cpp</filename> at column 15, line 25, "
"in an existing &kate; window, you could use:"
msgstr ""
"Če želite odpreti datoteko z imenom <filename>source.cpp</filename> v "
"stolpcu 15, vrstica 25, v obstoječem &kate; okno, lahko uporabite:"

#. Tag: screen
#: man-kate.1.docbook:153
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput><command>kate</command> <option>-c 15</option> <option>-l 25</"
"option> <filename>source.cpp</filename></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput><command>kate</command> <option>-c 15</option> <option>-l 25</"
"option> <filename>source.cpp</filename></userinput>"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:155
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have an active internet connection, you can take advantage of &kde;'s "
"network transparency to open a file from an &FTP; site. If you do not have "
"write permission on the remote server, the file will be opened read only and "
"you will be prompted for a local filename to save to if you make changes. If "
"you do have write permission, changes will be saved transparently over the "
"network."
msgstr ""
"Če imate aktivno internetno povezavo, lahko izkoristite omrežno preglednost "
"&kde; in odprete datoteko iz &FTP; mesto. Če nimate dovoljenja za pisanje na "
"oddaljenem strežniku, bo datoteka odprta samo za branje in pozvani boste k "
"lokalnemu imenu datoteke, v katerega želite shraniti, če naredite spremembe. "
"Če imate dovoljenje za pisanje, bodo spremembe pregledno shranjene prek "
"omrežja."

#. Tag: screen
#: man-kate.1.docbook:161
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput><command>kate</command> <option><replaceable>&kde-ftp;README</"
"replaceable></option></userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput><command>kate</command> <option><replaceable>&kde-ftp;README</"
"replaceable></option></userinput>"

#. Tag: title
#: man-kate.1.docbook:179
#, no-c-format
msgid "Authors"
msgstr "Avtorji"

#. Tag: para
#: man-kate.1.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The maintainer of &kate; is &Christoph.Cullmann; &Christoph.Cullmann.mail;. "
"A comprehensive list of authors and contributors is available in the "
"complete user manual mentioned above."
msgstr ""
"Vzdrževalec &kate; je &Christoph.Cullmann; &Christoph.Cullmann.mail;. "
"Obsežen seznam avtorjev in sodelavcev je na voljo v celotnem uporabniškem "
"priročniku, omenjenem zgoraj."
